# 📞 LegitCheck – Verify Official Campaign Numbers

LegitCheck is a simple Streamlit app that helps users verify if a phone number is part of an official government or company outreach campaign. Inspired by real-world experiences with legitimate but suspicious-looking communications, the tool aims to provide peace of mind at moments of doubt.

---

## 🚀 Features

- ✅ Check if a phone number is part of a known campaign (e.g. MOM surveys, OCBC card services, SIA payment lines)
- 📆 Shows campaign period and agency name
- ❓ Clear labels: Verified / Not Found
- 🔗 External link to the official agency or company site for follow-up

---

## 🧱 File Structure
GIT2025/
├── app/
│ ├── main.py # Streamlit app
│ └── utils.py # Logic for matching and date validation
├── data/
│ └── campaigns.json # List of verified campaign numbers
└── README.md # This file


---

## 🛠️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Create a virtual environment (recommended)

```bash
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

### 2. Install dependencies

pip install streamlit


### 3. Run the app
From the root GIT2025/ directory:
streamlit run app/main.py


📋 Example Campaigns in campaigns.json
63207777 → MOM CLFHS 2025 (Mar–Jul 2025)
62238888 → Singapore Airlines payment line
65357677 → OCBC card suspension hotline

🔍 Future Ideas
SMS message keyword scanner (e.g. “urgent”, “card suspended”)

Fuzzy number matching (e.g. partial number input)

Google Search or OpenAI API integration for company name lookup

Educational tips: “Don’t share OTPs” / “Call the agency directly”
